The Individual Combat-Special Purpose Rifle

Beautiful Spiral Fluted 14.7” Barrel (16.1” total with flash hider)

Color: Anodized Black Caliber: 5.56 NATO/.223 Rem.
Here is a Brand New in Box LWRC IC-SPR. Just arrived from the factory. This carbine has longer handrails and a self adjusting piston system. The previous IC had a shorter handguard and a 2-position manually adjusting piston system. Both rifles come with fully ambidextrous lowers and the same barrels. The new IC-SPR has the handguard mounting coupling forged into the upper receiver, whereas the previous SPR had the coupling bolted on.

This rifle has a Beautiful 14.7” Spiral Fluted Barrel. The barrel not only looks good, but the fluting shaves 20% of the weight off the barrel. LWRC’s fluting also relieves the stress caused problems seen in conventional fluting. LWRC rifles and carbines utilize cold hammer forged barrels made of 41V45 steel alloy (per Mil-B-11995E) and treated with NiCorr surface conversion technology. The total barrel length is approx. 16.1” with the permanent A2 Birdcage flash hider.

The barrel has a NICOR treatment which extends barrel life to over 20,000 rounds. It has the LWRC Fire Control Group with the one-piece Fail Zero coated bolt carrier and trigger.

The rifle has a six position adjustable stock, front and rear flip up sights, Magpul MIAD pistol grip and LWRC rail system with full length top rail. The piston system is self-adjusting. Bottom and side rails are included. Also included is one 30 PMag magazine (Gen M2 - 30 round), front sight adjustment tool, and owner’s manual.

All members of the IC family feature the new fully ambidextrous lower receiver. Dual controls for bolt catch and release, magazine release, and fire control mean that both right- and left-handed shooters can use the rifle to its full effectiveness. In addition, dual controls give shooters the option of using their offhand side to accommodate barriers or injury. They can effectively manipulate the controls without having to switch hands. Despite its dramatically improved functionality, this new dual control lower receiver is compatible with all legacy AR15 pattern upper receivers

The Monoforge™ upper receiver used in all members of the IC family is a further evolution of the M6A2-SPR platform introduced by LWRCI™ in 2011. It features a user-configurable rail system. Moreover, the mounting base for the handguard is machined as part of the upper receiver for added strength and reduced weight.
